    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "About ALSO.\n\nWe’re ALSO, an electric mobility company originally conceived as a part of Rivian. We’re a passionate team of builders, dreamers, doers and innovators, focused on creating entirely new (not to mention, innovative and delightful) vertically integrated, small EVs designed to meet the global mobility challenges of today and tomorrow. Our mission is to inspire everyone to ride ALSO—replacing many local car, truck and SUV miles with ones on vehicles that are more affordable, more enjoyable and 10-50x more efficient.\n\nALSO is looking for a Senior Battery Electronics Engineer to develop electronics systems for multiple micromobility platforms.\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\n - Directly Responsible Individual for developing the electrical battery hardware, define hardware and software features and requirements.\n\n - Drive PCBA development spanning sub-system architecture, schematic capture and layout, design characterization, validation and production ramp.\n\n - Plan schedule, development steps, test resources and contract manufacturer EOL activities.\n\n - Perform simulation, analysis and validation of critical circuits. Perform the worst case circuit analysis and determine corresponding validation.\n\n - Collaborate with mechanical teams on packaging and thermals.\n\n - Collaborate with firmware and control teams on HW integration and control strategies.\n\n - Work with systems engineering to author and ratify product requirements including cost, performance, reliability, regulatory, etc.\n\n - Work with functional safety peers to identify critical diagnostics/protection circuits and deliver appropriate design implementations.\n\n - Compile DFMEA, PFMEA and validation plans.\n\n - Perform hands on integration and test activities combined with directing and collaborating with test peers and outside resources such as certification labs and contract manufacturers.\n\nWhat You Will Bring\n\n - BS degree in Electrical Engineering or equivalent practical experience.\n\n - 4+ years working in board level design of battery powered electrical systems.\n\n - Excellent collaboration and communication skills in a highly collaborative role.\n\n - Knowledge of BMS hardware/software features and safety concepts.\n\n - Strong understanding of analog and digital circuits including microcontrollers and peripherals.\n\n - Proficiency with common simulation tools such as LT Spice.\n\n - Hands on experience with lab equipment and comfortable working with Li-ion batteries.\n\n - Experience delivering products to the market.\n\n\nThe salary for this position ranges from $160,000-$200,000 per year, depending on experience and qualifications.\n\nWhy ALSO.\n\nWe’re passionate about helping the world find a better way to get there—wherever it is you’re headed.\n\nWe’re located in the heart of Silicon Valley and have brought together a world-class team from some of the biggest brands in the technology, automotive, cycling, outdoor recreation and retail spaces. \n\nTogether we’re working hands-on to imagine, design and build an entirely new solution to a global set of transportation challenges. \n\nPerks and Benefits\n\n - Robust health coverage. Excellent health, dental and vision insurance covered up to 100% by ALSO with FSA \u0026 HSA options.\n\n - One Medical membership and dedicated insurance advocates.\n\n - Rich fertility and family building benefits with Progyny.\n\n - Flexible time off. \n\n - 401(k) match.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
